              OASIS-OPEN.org BOSTON, MA, USA; 14 MARCH 2005 --</strong> OASIS, the international e-business standards consortium, today announced that its members have approved the Security Assertion Markup Language (SAML) version 2.0 as an OASIS Standard, a status that signifies the highest level of ratification. SAML v2.0 enables the secure exchange of authentication, attribute, and authorization information between disparate security domains, making vendor-independent Web single sign-on and secure e-business transactions possible. Version 2.0 adds key functions to create and manage federated networks that combine and appropriately share pre-existing repositories of identity information....SAML provides a standard XML schema for specifying authentication,attribute, and authorization decision statements, and also specifies a Web services-based request/reply protocol for exchanging these statements....SAML leverages core Web services standards including XML, SOAP, Transport Layer Security (TLS), XML Signature (XMLSIG), and XML Encryption (XMLENC). ...<a href="http://www.oasis-open.org/news/oasis_news_03_14_05.php">Full Story</a></p>
